msgid "I was pulled into the pool with my clothes on. I panicked for a moment, but luckily my feet touched bottom."
msgstr "Caí a la piscina con la ropa puesta."

#: 01302:236
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Pah! Waph! What are you...Th-that's dangerous!\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"¡Oye!\n"
"¡Pero qué...!\""

#: 01302:240
msgid ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"..................\""
msgstr ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"...\""

#: 01302:241
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Ah...\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"¡¡...!!\""

#: 01302:242
msgid "When I came up to take a breath, I saw her staring at me."
msgstr "Cuando salí para tomar una bocanada de aire, me di cuenta de que me estaba mirando."

#: 01302:243
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Uh, umm...\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Ey...\""

#: 01302:246
# ¿Travieso? Quizá mejor pervertido o salido.
msgid ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"Pervert!\""
msgstr ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"¡Eres un salido!\""

#: 01302:247
msgid "She's still mad."
msgstr "Está enfadada."

#: 01302:248
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"I'm sorry......\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Lo siento.\""

#: 01302:251
msgid ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"......but, I forgive you.\""
msgstr ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"Pero... Te perdono.\""

#: 01302:252
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"You do?\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"¿En serio?\""

#: 01302:255
msgid ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"I don't have a choice!\""
msgstr ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"¡No me queda otra!\""

#: 01302:256
msgid "I don't know what made her feel better, but I'm so glad she forgave me."
msgstr "No sé qué hacer para que se sienta mejor, pero me alegro un montón de que me haya perdonado."

#: 01302:259
msgid ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"I'll try to get along, too, so you have to try and forget what you saw, OK?\""
msgstr ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"Lo intentaré. Pero tú también tienes que intentar olvidarlo, ¿vale?\""

#: 01302:260
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Y-yeah. I'll do my best.\n"
"Thanks, Hinata-san.\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Lo haré.\n"
"Gracias por aceptar mis disculpas.\""

#: 01302:263
# Hay que ver si en japonés, hace alguna referencia a ella en la frase anterior.
msgid ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"Call me Mizuki.\""
msgstr ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"Llámame Mizuki.\""

#: 01302:264
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"What do you mean?\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"¿Qué quieres decir?\""

#: 01302:265
msgid ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"It's my name! I'm not used to being called Hinata-san.\""
msgstr ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"No quiero que me llames por mi apellido.\""

#: 01302:266
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Oh, okay? Mizuki, huh?\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Está bien.\""

#: 01302:267
msgid "I got friendly permission to call her by her first name."
msgstr "Amistosamente, me dio permiso para llamarla por su nombre."

#: 01302:268
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Then you can call me Kazushi, too.\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Entonces, tú también puedes llamarme por mi nombre.\""

#: 01302:269
msgid ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"All right, Kazushi......\""
msgstr ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"Está bien,\n"
"Kazushi...\""

#: 01302:270
msgid "She offered me her hand and we shook in the pool."
msgstr "Me ofreció estrecharme la mano."

#: 01302:273
msgid ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"Friends again?\""
msgstr ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"¿Amigos?\""

#: 01302:274
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Friends.\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Amigos.\""

#: 01302:275
msgid "I shook her soft and unexpectedly big hand. With the sun and its reflection off the water, Mizuki glistened, like a pretty mermaid."
msgstr "Le estreché su suave e inesperada mano."

#: 01302:276
msgid "She looked so much more beautiful in the water than when I see her in the class room."
msgstr "Parecía mucho más guapa en el agua que cuando la veo en clase."

#: 01302:277
msgid "She truly looks like a mermaid. My first impression wasn't that off after all."
msgstr "Realmente parece una sirenita."

#: 01302:280
msgid ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"Can I ask you something, since we're friends?\""
msgstr ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"¿Puedo preguntarte algo?\""

#: 01302:281
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"What is it?\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"¿Qué pasa?\""

#: 01302:284
msgid ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"You can't swim, can you?\""
msgstr ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"No sabes nadar. ¿Verdad?\""

#: 01302:285
msgid "Bull's eye."
msgstr "Tiene razón."

#: 01302:286
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Actually......\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"La verdad...\""

#: 01302:287
msgid "To tell you the truth, I can only swim about 5 meters."
msgstr "A decir verdad, sólo logro nadar unos diez metros."

#: 01302:288
msgid ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"I knew it.\n"
"And I have a policy of not making friends with people who can't swim.\""
msgstr ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"Lo sabía.\n"
"Y tengo por norma no tener amigos que no sepan nadar.\""

#: 01302:289
msgid "She gripped my hand tightly as we continued to shake."
msgstr "Me soltó la mano."

#: 01302:290
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"You do......?\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"¿Ah, sí...?\""

#: 01302:293
msgid ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"I'll just have to teach you how to swim, then. Don't worry; you'll swim in no time. Every human starts to swim naturally if they're about to die.\""
msgstr ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"Te enseñaré a nadar. No te preocupes. Todos hemos nacido con la capacidad de nadar.\""

#: 01302:294
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"I'll be on the verge of death?\""
msgstr ""

#: 01302:295
msgid "I was glad that we had become friends, but it looked like she might kill me. Is this good or bad?"
msgstr "Espero que tenga suficiente paciencia conmigo."

#: 01302:296
msgid "Well, I can just hide from her for a while."
msgstr "O ya podré esconderme de ella durante un tiempo."
